text: Portsmouth is a city in Rockingham County, New Hampshire, in the United States. It is the only city in the county, but only the fourth-largest community.The Rockingham County towns (not cities) of Derry (34,317), Salem (30,089), and Londonderry (25,826) had greater populations according to the 2020 census. It has a population of 21,956 at the 2020 census. ==References== Category:Cities in New Hampshire
title: Portsmouth, New Hampshire
